  "title": "ServiceNow Developer (Ref 26328)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Configure and support packaged or SaaS applications to adapt features, manage releases, and maintain system stability</li><li>Utilize standard tools, APIs, and low-code platforms to develop solutions that meet business requirements while ensuring compatibility and performance</li><li>Serve as a subject matter expert and lead the team to deliver effective application support and development</li><li>Lead and participate in cross-functional team meetings to align on project goals and key decisions</li><li>Provide innovative solutions to technical problems affecting your team and multiple teams</li><li>Develop and implement enhancements that improve user experience and system performance</li><li>Conduct thorough testing and validation of applications to ensure quality, reliability, and compliance with standards</li><li>Mentor and guide junior team members to support their professional development and team capability</li><li>Continuously evaluate and apply best practices in application development and support to optimize processes and outcomes</li><li>Master proficiency in ServiceNow Customer Service Management (CSM) to support platform-specific needs</li></ul><p>Requirements</p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Science, Engineering, or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 3-4 years of experience in information technology</li></ul><p>Preferred competencies and qualifications</p><ul><li>Advanced proficiency in Packaged Development Estimating, Packaged Application Integration, SaaS Testing, and Software Platforms</li></ul><p><br />Licence no: 12C6060</p>",
